{{Quote|...I was supposed to be rotated back to my homeworld and discharged a civilian at the end of it. That was... five? six? hitches ago. I lost track"<br />"Imslow.|Captain Dr. [[Kornell Divini]] and Commander [[Hotise]]|<ref name="Death Star (novel)">[[Death Star (novel)|''Death Star'']]</ref>}}
The '''Imperial Military Stop Loss Order''', abbreviated '''IMSLO''', was a retroactive [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] directive. It mandated that all beings conscripted into military service be required to stay in service as long as the Empire wished it. Skilled [[Specialist/Legends|specialists]], and [[Doctor/Legends|doctors]] in particular, were often retained in Imperial service under the IMSLO.

Some unhappy members of the [[Imperial Military/Legends|Imperial Military]], affected by the IMSLO, created a [[Wikipedia:backronym|backronym]]: "I'm Milking Scragged; Life's Over."

